\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Robustness (left) and susceptibility (right) for base and misaligned variants of the four models. Error bars denote standard errors. Misaligned variants uniformly cluster in a narrow low-robustness band ($R \approx 2.5$--$4.7$) regardless of their base model's robustness, and all show elevated susceptibility. For reference, the 17 non-misaligned models benchmarked by \citet  {costa2025moral} span $R \in [3.2, 122.2]$ and $S \in [0.61, 0.96]$.}}{6}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:bars}{{2}{6}{Robustness (left) and susceptibility (right) for base and misaligned variants of the four models. Error bars denote standard errors. Misaligned variants uniformly cluster in a narrow low-robustness band ($R \approx 2.5$--$4.7$) regardless of their base model's robustness, and all show elevated susceptibility. For reference, the 17 non-misaligned models benchmarked by \citet {costa2025moral} span $R \in [3.2, 122.2]$ and $S \in [0.61, 0.96]$}{figure.2}{}}
